# 🚨 Fraud Detection Pipeline

An automated CI/CD pipeline that ingests banking transaction data, applies fraud detection rules, flags suspicious transactions, stores results in AWS DynamoDB, and sends real-time email alerts via AWS SNS. The entire system is containerized with Docker and deployed on AWS EC2 through a Jenkins pipeline.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project simulates a real-world banking fraud detection system. Transaction data is uploaded to AWS S3, processed by a Python rules engine, and flagged transactions are automatically stored in DynamoDB and trigger email alerts via SNS. Every code push to GitHub automatically triggers the full CI/CD pipeline — from testing to deployment — with zero manual intervention.

---

